# #1010 (secondary): a builtin call whose argument COUNT is valid but whose argument TYPES
# match no overload must report a type/overload mismatch, not a self-contradictory arity
# message. zip accepts 2 iterables, so the count (2) is in range; ints are not iterable, so
# no overload's types match (Python raises "argument ... is not iterable" here too).
def main() -> None:
    print(zip(1, 2))
